HEADWORD: Choragic
<hw>Cho*rag"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/,
<?/.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a choragus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Choragic monument</b></col>, <cd>a building or column
built by a victorious choragus for the reception and exhibition of the
tripod which he received as a prize. Those of Lysicrates and Thrasyllus
are still to be seen at Athens.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Choragus</ent>⟦br⟧
